column1: Data Description: Willow seedling transplant survival and growth survey
Names of Data Takers:  Jane Smith, Riva Madan, Connor Bernard, Sam Sartwell, Jared Huxley

Column Info: all variables measurements are in cm; 'variables'  measured for each transplanted willow seedling were: 'ht1' =  willow height to the tip of the stem (including new green stem growth and buds), 'ht2' = willow height to the tip of the highest leaf, pulling the leaf up to measure, 'cnpy1' = width of longest axis of shrub canopy looking down from above, 'cnpy2' = width of canopy axis perpendicular to cnpy1; willow seedlings were transplanted into plots in 2007 (w_1-10) and 2006 (w_A-C)

Abbreviations & Definitions: 'code' = plot treatment in which the first letter indicates snow addition (P), second letter nitrogen addition (N), and third letter temp warming (W), where 'X' = control treatment for each of the three factors; 'w_1-10' are willow transplant numbers 1-10 and 'w_A-C' are willow transplants A-C; 'dead' = confirmed dead, 'dead' = can't find
column headers: block, plot, code, snow, n, temp, variable, w_1-10, w_A-C

column13: broken off dead stem found in this location, so probably dead
